crumble /ˈkrʌmbəl/

(crumbling,crumbled,crumbles) 

1. V-T/V-I If something crumbles , or if you crumble it, it breaks into a lot of small pieces. 碎裂; 弄碎 

例： Under the pressure, the flint crumbled into fragments. 在压力作用下，燧石裂成了碎片。 

2. V-I If an old building or piece of land is crumbling , parts of it keep breaking off. 崩塌 

例： The high- and low-rise apartment blocks built in the 1960s are crumbling. 建于20世纪60年代的高、低层公寓楼正摇摇欲坠。 

3. PHRASAL VERB Crumble away means the same as . 崩塌 

例： Much of the coastline is crumbling away. 多处海岸线正在垮塌。 

4. V-I If something such as a system, relationship, or hope crumbles , it comes to an end. (制度、关系或希望) 崩溃 

例： Their economy crumbled under the weight of United Nations sanctions. 在联合国制裁的重压之下，他们的经济崩溃了。 

5. PHRASAL VERB Crumble away means the same as . (制度、关系或希望) 崩溃 

例： Opposition more or less crumbled away. 反对党差不多崩溃了。

